03:07.220 --> 03:08.517
- Sure, Al.
- You know Evelyn, my date?

03:08.655 --> 03:09.781
- Yeah?
- She's a schoolteacher,

03:09.923 --> 03:11.687
and she wouldn't like it
if I was tardy.

03:11.825 --> 03:13.520
(laughs)
Tardy. Oh, Al?

03:13.660 --> 03:14.650
- Al...
- Yep?

03:14.795 --> 03:15.990
Ought to bring her an apple.

03:16.129 --> 03:18.325
- I got it in the car.
- Oh, great.

03:18.465 --> 03:19.694
Have a good time.

03:19.833 --> 03:21.460
Joanie, lock up for me, okay?

03:21.601 --> 03:24.070
Uh, no thanks, big brother.

03:24.204 --> 03:25.933
Smitty's going to show me
the Big Dipper

03:26.073 --> 03:27.336
through his telescope.

03:27.474 --> 03:29.602
Tell the folks I'll be home
a little later.

03:29.743 --> 03:30.972
- See you.
- Bye.

03:31.111 --> 03:33.170
Joanie, Mom and Dad
are never going to buy

03:33.313 --> 03:35.077
that Big Dipper bit.

03:35.215 --> 03:38.515
They bought it when we used it,
Sizzle Lips.

03:38.652 --> 03:39.949
That's true.

03:40.087 --> 03:41.885
Of course,
I carried a telescope.

03:42.022 --> 03:42.989
Let's go.

03:43.123 --> 03:45.182
Ralph, sure you don't want

03:45.325 --> 03:46.656
to join us
for some Chinese food?

03:46.793 --> 03:48.420
Oh, no thanks,
I got a hot date tonight.

03:48.562 --> 03:50.223
She doesn't like Chinese food.

03:50.363 --> 03:52.559
When she was a baby she was
frightened by an egg foo yung.

03:52.699 --> 03:53.825
(laughter)

03:53.967 --> 03:55.662
Do you know how to make
an egg foo yung?

03:55.802 --> 03:57.793
- How?
- Take a young egg and foo it.

03:57.938 --> 03:59.133
(laughter)

03:59.272 --> 04:00.740
No date, huh?

04:00.874 --> 04:02.103
No.

04:02.242 --> 04:03.641
Well, then you lock up.

04:03.777 --> 04:04.972
- Take it easy.
- Right. -See you.

04:05.112 --> 04:06.671
- Potsie?
- Yeah?

04:06.813 --> 04:08.804
Are you ready
for a little moo goo gai pan?

04:08.949 --> 04:10.576
(chuckles)
You bet,

04:10.717 --> 04:12.651
but let's eat first.

04:18.591 --> 04:21.185
Well, here we are again,

04:21.327 --> 04:23.160
all alone,

04:23.296 --> 04:25.230
just the two of us.

04:28.101 --> 04:29.159
Oh!

04:29.302 --> 04:31.202
You're kind
of jumpy tonight, Malph.

04:31.338 --> 04:32.828
Fonz, what are you doing here?

04:32.973 --> 04:34.407
Everybody's got to be someplace.

04:34.541 --> 04:35.508
(chuckles)
Good one!

04:35.642 --> 04:37.007
Yeah, I know, I know.

04:37.144 --> 04:38.236
Where is everybody?

04:38.378 --> 04:40.005
Oh, um, Al had a date,

04:40.147 --> 04:42.548
and everyone else went
to a Chinese restaurant.

04:42.682 --> 04:44.013
I would have gone too, Fonz,

04:44.151 --> 04:46.210
but my date doesn't
like Chinese food.

04:46.353 --> 04:47.479
When she was a baby...

04:47.621 --> 04:48.952
No date, huh, Malph?

04:49.089 --> 04:51.114
No, Fonz.

04:51.258 --> 04:53.488
Okay, what's the matter,
Ralphie?

04:53.627 --> 04:54.788
Nothing's the matter, Fonz.

04:54.928 --> 04:56.418
(snaps)
Spill it.

04:57.764 --> 04:59.323
All right, Fonz.

04:59.466 --> 05:01.628
It's-it's about the girls
I've been dating.

05:01.768 --> 05:05.432
You see, they-they only go out
with me for one thing.

05:05.572 --> 05:07.404
I know the feeling.

05:07.541 --> 05:09.270
It's not that, Fonz.

05:09.409 --> 05:12.379
I wish it was that.

05:12.512 --> 05:14.981
Girls only go out with me
for laughs.

05:15.115 --> 05:17.982
There's another side
to me, Fonz, you know?

05:18.118 --> 05:21.713
And I'm just tired of being
the funniest guy in town.

05:21.855 --> 05:22.947
And the expense...

05:23.089 --> 05:24.250
Do you know what it costs
these days

05:24.391 --> 05:25.654
for a good dribble glass?

05:26.893 --> 05:28.258
I don't know, I'd just,

05:28.395 --> 05:31.888
just kind of like it if
someone would take me seriously.

05:32.032 --> 05:34.558
Hey, listen,
I totally understand, you know?

05:34.701 --> 05:36.601
Now if that's what you want,

05:36.736 --> 05:38.067
you've got to get rid of these.

05:38.205 --> 05:40.105
You've got to throw them away.

05:42.108 --> 05:44.736
Oh, Fonz!

05:44.878 --> 05:46.243
I've got to...

05:46.379 --> 05:48.108
I've got to taper off, you know.

05:48.248 --> 05:49.682
I can't just quit cold turkey.

05:49.816 --> 05:51.580
Cold turkey.

05:51.718 --> 05:53.482
- Yeah?
- That's right.

