Oh, hi, Ralph.

06:08.268 --> 06:10.100
Oh, hey, Leather.

06:10.237 --> 06:11.227
How's it going'?

06:11.371 --> 06:12.429
All right.

06:12.572 --> 06:13.767
You all by your lonesome?

06:13.907 --> 06:15.306
(chuckles)
Yeah.

06:15.442 --> 06:16.773
All by my lonesome.

06:16.910 --> 06:18.378
Speaking of lonesome,

06:18.511 --> 06:20.605
I heard about a guy
who's so lone...

06:20.747 --> 06:22.977
No jokes, Ralph, no jokes.

06:23.884 --> 06:25.318
Yeah, I'm all alone tonight,
Leather.

06:25.452 --> 06:28.717
Yep, all alone, all alone,
alone, alone, alone.

06:28.855 --> 06:30.755
How about you?

06:30.891 --> 06:31.881
No date tonight?

06:32.025 --> 06:33.117
Nah.

06:33.260 --> 06:34.386
By the time I finish singing,

06:34.527 --> 06:35.585
everybody's already paired off,

06:35.729 --> 06:39.393
and I get stuck with my,
uh, partner here.

06:39.532 --> 06:41.864
Yeah, I just ditched my partner.

06:42.869 --> 06:44.894
You know, Ralph,

06:45.038 --> 06:46.938
something's been
bugging me lately.

06:47.073 --> 06:49.371
Well, for some reason,

06:49.509 --> 06:52.103
guys seem to shy away from me.

06:52.245 --> 06:54.236
Maybe I scare them.

06:54.381 --> 06:55.746
Oh. yeah?

06:55.882 --> 06:58.613
I guess I might be scared of you
if I didn't know you.

06:58.752 --> 07:00.083
I mean, you're on your own,

07:00.220 --> 07:01.449
you're more mature,

07:01.588 --> 07:02.817
you wear a lot of leather.

07:05.358 --> 07:06.587
Yeah, I guess that's true,

07:06.726 --> 07:10.253
(chuckles) but it sure makes
for lonely evenings.

07:10.397 --> 07:12.388
Yeah.

07:13.400 --> 07:14.834
Hey, look at this,

07:14.968 --> 07:16.936
we're having
a serious discussion here.

07:17.070 --> 07:18.003
Oh, I'm sorry.

07:18.138 --> 07:20.300
No, no, I like that.

07:20.440 --> 07:22.101
Say, Leather, uh,

07:22.242 --> 07:25.940
you know next week is, uh,
having the Military Ball

07:26.079 --> 07:27.706
at the college, you know,

07:27.847 --> 07:29.906
and I was thinking
maybe you'd... (chuckles)

07:30.050 --> 07:32.781
Would you like to, um,
be my date?

07:34.354 --> 07:37.324
Well, it's going to be really,
really great, Leather.

07:37.457 --> 07:40.119
I mean, it's this
big special formal dance.

07:40.260 --> 07:41.853
They have it every year.

07:41.995 --> 07:43.224
It sounds like fun.

07:43.363 --> 07:44.558
I'd love to go.

07:44.698 --> 07:46.427
Great! Then it's a date.

07:46.566 --> 07:48.432
It's a date!

07:48.568 --> 07:50.559
All right.

07:55.675 --> 08:03.139
W-E-E-N-I-E.

08:03.283 --> 08:05.274
Weenie!

08:06.720 --> 08:08.916
That's nine points, Marion,

08:09.055 --> 08:11.046
and I hope I don't see
any more E's.

08:11.191 --> 08:13.990
Oh, that's very good, Howard.

08:14.127 --> 08:15.117
Yeah.

08:15.261 --> 08:16.751
Uh, jonquil.

08:16.896 --> 08:18.022
Now let's see, let's see,

08:18.164 --> 08:20.633
now that's double letter score
for the Q,

08:20.767 --> 08:24.965
uh, so that makes 33 times three
for triple letter score...

08:25.105 --> 08:27.733
and 50 for using
all seven letters,

08:27.874 --> 08:29.808
and my L makes lover
out of over,

08:29.943 --> 08:32.105
so that's a 157 points.

08:32.245 --> 08:35.977
That's the second best play
I've had tonight.

08:36.116 --> 08:38.482
This is really fun, Howard.

08:40.754 --> 08:42.347
Game is over, Marion.

08:42.489 --> 08:43.888
I don't want to play anymore.

08:44.024 --> 08:45.822
Oh, look at,

08:45.959 --> 08:48.860
you've got X-I-P-H-0-I-D,
xiphoid.

08:48.995 --> 08:50.520
Oh, you would have had
so many scores.

08:50.663 --> 08:51.630
Really?

08:51.765 --> 08:53.824
- Too bad, game's over.
- Wait!

08:54.834 --> 08:56.563
Well, you go and watch
Jack Parr.

08:56.703 --> 08:58.694
-(doorbell rings)
- I'll get it.

09:00.573 --> 09:01.563
- Oh, hi, Leather.
- Hi.

09:01.708 --> 09:03.005
- Come on in.
- Oh, Leather.

09:03.143 --> 09:04.304
I saw the lights on.

09:04.444 --> 09:06.572
I hope I'm not interrupting
anything.

09:06.713 --> 09:07.942
(chuckles)
Bang, bang.

09:08.081 --> 09:09.242
No, no.

09:09.382 --> 09:11.680
Howard was just going
to turn on Jack Parr.

09:11.818 --> 09:14.913
He loves to watch Parr cry.

09:15.055 --> 09:16.887
Mrs. C., uh,

09:17.023 --> 09:19.082
I-I need to talk to you
about a couple of things.

09:19.225 --> 09:21.785
Oh, good, I love to talk.

09:21.928 --> 09:25.125
Okay, you two talk.

09:25.265 --> 09:28.895
I'll be down after the show.

09:29.035 --> 09:31.561
He can watch Parr cry
on the upstairs set.

09:31.704 --> 09:34.765
Now, what do you want
to talk about?

09:34.908 --> 09:37.878
Well, Mrs. C.,
I want to become a woman.

09:38.011 --> 09:40.105
I've been invited
to this college dance,

09:40.246 --> 09:42.977
and I don't even know what kind
of dress I should wear.

09:43.116 --> 09:44.777
Does it have to be leather?

09:44.918 --> 09:46.249
No.

09:46.386 --> 09:48.445
It's a fancy dance,
a Military Ball,

09:48.588 --> 09:50.249
and I have a date
with Ralph Malph.

09:50.390 --> 09:52.586
Better get something
wash and dry.

09:52.725 --> 09:55.092
I don't even know
if I should go.

09:55.228 --> 09:57.993
I won't know how to act.

09:58.131 --> 09:59.326
What nonsense.

09:59.466 --> 10:00.627
You can do it.

10:00.767 --> 10:02.599
You stay in our guest room
for one week.

10:02.735 --> 10:05.136
I'll teach you;
you'll just be fine.

10:05.271 --> 10:06.966
Now first,

10:07.107 --> 10:09.337
sitting.

10:10.677 --> 10:12.668
<i>II</i>

10:40.707 --> 10:42.698
<i>II</i>

11:09.736 --> 11:11.727
<i>II</i>

11:13.740 --> 11:16.266
<i>HOWARD: Well Marion,
We got to hand it to you.</i>

11:16.409 --> 11:18.241
<i>You really worked hard
this week,</i>

11:18.378 --> 11:20.710
<i>and you did a terrific job
with Leather.</i>

11:20.847 --> 11:23.509
Oh, come on, dear, everybody is
so busy with the dance.

11:23.650 --> 11:25.175
It's just going to be
you and me.

11:25.318 --> 11:26.410
Well, that's perfect.

11:26.553 --> 11:28.453
We'll have a nice,
quiet meal together.

11:28.588 --> 11:30.579
Dig in.

11:32.659 --> 11:35.890
It's all right, sweetheart,
I'll peel back the foil.

11:36.029 --> 11:37.519
Mom, Mom, come quick.

11:37.664 --> 11:38.631
Leather broke her heel.

11:38.765 --> 11:40.290
- Come on, hurry.
- Oh, dear.

11:40.433 --> 11:42.424
I told her to walk on her toes!

11:42.569 --> 11:44.537
Well, I guess I'll have

11:44.671 --> 11:47.106
a nice quiet meal all by myself.

11:48.508 --> 11:51.443
Oh, Howard, you poor dear.

11:51.578 --> 11:53.569
Just for that,

11:53.713 --> 11:55.340
why don't you start off

11:55.481 --> 11:59.475
with a nice piece of cake?

12:00.587 --> 12:03.921
Why thank you, Marion.

12:04.057 --> 12:07.584
Emblems, gold, I, uh,
lost, can't find,

12:07.727 --> 12:10.321
you know, little eagles, claws.

12:10.463 --> 12:11.828
Yeah, I know what eagles
look like, Richard.

12:11.965 --> 12:13.956
I can't... I need them,
uh, regulations.

12:14.968 --> 12:16.766
Maybe they're in the car.

12:16.903 --> 12:18.496
No, no, wait!

12:18.638 --> 12:20.834
Maybe they're in the car.

12:22.375 --> 12:23.399
JOANIE:
Dad,

12:23.543 --> 12:24.408
Dad, quick, hammer.

12:24.544 --> 12:25.534
Kitchen drawer.

12:25.678 --> 12:28.670
Right.

12:28.815 --> 12:30.715
I found one.

12:30.850 --> 12:32.011
Back seat.

12:32.151 --> 12:33.983
Lori Beth. (laughs)

12:34.120 --> 12:35.952
I'll just put this one

12:36.089 --> 12:37.454
where it's supposed to and then

12:37.590 --> 12:39.115
I'll-I'll put my chin
over the other place.

12:39.259 --> 12:40.988
- No one will notice.
- Richard, I found your button!

12:41.127 --> 12:42.117
- Oh, great. Great.
-(doorbell rings)

12:42.262 --> 12:45.061
I got it.

12:45.198 --> 12:46.393
- Good evening, Richard.
- Oh.

12:46.532 --> 12:47.693
For me? (laughs)

12:47.834 --> 12:48.858
Always clowning.

12:49.002 --> 12:50.401
I can't stand around.

12:50.536 --> 12:53.301
Mom found
my other little button.

12:53.439 --> 12:54.929
Is Leather ready?

12:55.074 --> 12:57.065
Uh, uh, most of her.

13:02.548 --> 13:04.949
Good evening, Mr. Cunningham.

13:05.084 --> 13:06.609
At ease, Malph.

13:06.753 --> 13:08.778
Yes, thank you, sir.

13:08.921 --> 13:11.253
Well, got to hurry up.

13:11.391 --> 13:12.449
Pick up Lori Beth.

13:12.592 --> 13:14.253
See you at the dance, Fly Boy.

13:14.394 --> 13:16.658
(chuckles)
Fly Boy.

13:16.796 --> 13:19.197
Hey, aren't you going to
even call me Dog Face?

13:19.332 --> 13:20.322
No.

13:20.466 --> 13:21.763
You're such a card.

13:21.901 --> 13:23.630
Well, see you.

13:26.773 --> 13:28.764
Now enjoy your dinner, dear.

13:32.178 --> 13:34.044
Forgot corsage!

13:34.180 --> 13:35.841
(stammering)

13:35.982 --> 13:38.110
Ah, found corsage.

13:38.251 --> 13:40.720
Pretty.

13:53.533 --> 13:55.900
Da-da-da-da-da-da!

13:56.035 --> 13:59.733
Gentlemen, presenting
Miss Leather Tuscadero!

14:13.319 --> 14:14.411
Leather,

14:14.554 --> 14:16.318
you look beautiful.

14:24.230 --> 14:26.324
(slow music playing)

14:46.219 --> 14:48.551
Will the owner
of a gray aircraft carrier,

14:48.688 --> 14:50.588
license number, V-E-V-J,

14:50.723 --> 14:52.122
please report to the bandstand.

14:52.258 --> 14:54.090
You've been torpedoed.

14:54.227 --> 14:55.285
(groaning laughter)

14:55.428 --> 14:57.055
But seriously, servicemen,

14:57.196 --> 15:00.325
the Society
of R.0.T.C. Scabbard and Blade

15:00.466 --> 15:02.958
is, uh, pleased to announce
for your entertainment

15:03.102 --> 15:06.265
Midshipman Potsie Weber
and Miss Jennifer Jerome.

15:06.406 --> 15:07.703
(applause)

15:14.514 --> 15:15.879
You were great, Rich.

15:16.015 --> 15:18.074
I think I bombed.

15:18.217 --> 15:20.515
