17:05.525 --> 17:06.685
POTSIE:
Hey, guys, there's Malph.

17:06.826 --> 17:08.521
Oh, doesn't Leather
look wonderful!

17:08.661 --> 17:10.925
- Yeah, come on.
- Yeah, come on.

17:11.063 --> 17:12.895
- Leather, you look gorgeous!
- You look fantastic!

17:13.031 --> 17:14.363
- Fantastic.
- Oh, beautiful.

17:14.500 --> 17:16.559
Hey, Malph, Malph,
bring the marshmallows?

17:16.702 --> 17:18.636
You see, last year Ralph
stuck marshmallows

17:18.771 --> 17:19.965
on everybody's sword.

17:20.106 --> 17:21.232
- It was good. Remember?
- Oh, yeah.

17:21.374 --> 17:23.775
I tell you, at a formal affair,
this man has got it.

17:23.910 --> 17:24.843
- He really does, I tell you...
- Sure does.

17:24.977 --> 17:26.308
Gentlemen,

17:26.444 --> 17:27.878
I've outgrown
that sort of thing.

17:28.013 --> 17:28.947
Yes.

17:29.081 --> 17:30.571
Look at the orchid Ralph
gave me.

17:30.716 --> 17:31.911
Does it squirt?

17:32.051 --> 17:33.815
Punch, Leather?

17:33.953 --> 17:35.512
Thank you, Ralph.

17:35.655 --> 17:37.646
"Does it squirt?"

17:39.158 --> 17:41.286
Isn't Ralph acting
a little funny?

17:41.427 --> 17:43.486
- Funny is what he isn't acting.
- Yeah.

17:44.497 --> 17:46.488
Punch?

17:48.901 --> 17:50.767
(laughing loudly)

17:50.903 --> 17:52.803
Ralph!
That's a great one, Malph!

17:52.939 --> 17:54.236
A fly in an ice cube.

17:54.373 --> 17:56.307
-(laughter)
- See that?

17:56.442 --> 17:58.604
Ralph would do that.

17:58.744 --> 17:59.836
(cackles)
I wish I'd thought...

17:59.979 --> 18:01.640
That's not funny.

18:02.682 --> 18:04.878
Ralph, you didn't
put that in there?

18:05.017 --> 18:06.883
Of course not.

18:10.456 --> 18:11.548
What time is it?

18:11.691 --> 18:13.318
Oh, I don't know. Why?

18:13.459 --> 18:15.450
Well, we've got to get
out of here by midnight.

18:15.595 --> 18:18.223
Yeah, but we don't have to be
in till 1:00.

18:18.364 --> 18:21.629
Yowza, yowza, yowza.

18:21.767 --> 18:23.599
You bet.

18:23.736 --> 18:25.329
I hear where Cuba
is breaking off

18:25.471 --> 18:27.667
all diplomatic ties
with the U.S.

18:30.443 --> 18:32.673
Who wants to go
to Europe, anyway?

18:35.348 --> 18:38.579
RICHIE: Thank you,
Dewey and the Studebakers.

18:38.718 --> 18:41.278
Now, on to the highlight
of the entire evening.

18:41.420 --> 18:43.149
If the honor guard will take
their positions now,

18:43.289 --> 18:46.782
we can begin our annual
Scabbard and Blade procession.

18:46.926 --> 18:48.451
And don't forget, guys,
comb your hair,

18:48.594 --> 18:50.187
because they're taking pictures
for the year book.

18:50.329 --> 18:52.320
Okay.

18:56.502 --> 18:57.594
You ready, Lori Beth, ready?

18:57.737 --> 18:59.603
All set, Sizzle Lips.

18:59.739 --> 19:02.174
Ralph, wait till you see
what these two are going to do.

19:02.308 --> 19:03.400
When they walk through the line,

19:03.542 --> 19:04.839
they're going to tickle
the guards!

19:04.977 --> 19:07.139
- Yeah! All right.
- Let's go.

19:07.279 --> 19:09.373
How juvenile.

19:09.515 --> 19:11.506
And unladylike.

19:34.173 --> 19:35.607
Ready?

19:35.741 --> 19:37.732
(laughter)

19:43.816 --> 19:45.215
<i>Atten-hut'.!</i>

19:45.351 --> 19:46.477
(chuckles)

19:46.619 --> 19:48.212
No, no, not me! Not me!

19:48.354 --> 19:49.617
You be careful!

19:49.755 --> 19:52.486
That's great.

19:52.625 --> 19:54.354
Well, that was fun.

19:54.493 --> 19:55.858
I never walked
under swords before.

19:55.995 --> 19:57.588
Yeah, I could have died

19:57.730 --> 19:59.425
when Rich and Lori Beth
tickled the guards.

19:59.565 --> 20:01.158
Oh, wasn't that great, Malph?

20:01.300 --> 20:03.860
Yes, it could be construed
as funny.

20:04.003 --> 20:05.971
The old Ralph Malph
might have thought so.

20:06.105 --> 20:09.336
But the new me has changed
quite considerably.

20:09.475 --> 20:10.738
I like the new you, Ralph,

20:10.876 --> 20:12.241
-quite considerably.
- Yeah.

20:12.378 --> 20:14.369
If that's the way you want
to be, that's fine with us.

20:14.513 --> 20:16.242
Yeah. Even if it does take
a little getting used to.

20:16.382 --> 20:17.508
(chuckles)

20:17.650 --> 20:19.880
Does the new Ralph get hungry

20:20.019 --> 20:21.544
like the old Ralph used to?

20:21.687 --> 20:22.984
We're all human, my dear.

20:23.122 --> 20:26.023
Food is life, and life is food.

20:26.158 --> 20:27.751
Hey, listen, I've got an idea.

20:27.893 --> 20:29.952
This is the last dance anyway,
so let's, uh,

20:30.096 --> 20:32.724
have some shishkebob!

20:32.865 --> 20:34.731
Hey, good idea, yeah.

20:34.867 --> 20:36.665
We're going to have
to pass on that, Richard.

20:36.802 --> 20:39.294
Leather and I were planning
on a quiet supper.

20:39.438 --> 20:41.099
- Well, have a good time.
- Okay, take it easy.

20:41.240 --> 20:42.173
- Enjoy your shishkebob.
- Good-bye.

20:42.308 --> 20:43.400
Okay, good night.

20:43.542 --> 20:45.032
Hey, Rich, Rich!

20:45.177 --> 20:47.168
-(shouting, laughter)
-(balloons popping)

20:54.186 --> 20:55.745
(laughter)

20:55.888 --> 20:57.754
Oh, you're so funny.

21:00.259 --> 21:02.023
Did you see where Cuba
is breaking off

21:02.161 --> 21:04.926
all diplomatic ties
with the U.S.?

21:12.271 --> 21:13.932
Well, maybe tomorrow night

21:14.073 --> 21:15.802
you can teach me
another new game, dear.

21:15.941 --> 21:17.602
I mean, learning is such fun.

21:17.743 --> 21:20.838
Marion, would you just keep
your mind on the game, please?

21:20.980 --> 21:22.971
Come on, it's your move.

21:26.886 --> 21:28.354
Gin.

21:32.925 --> 21:35.189
You know, Howard,
that was so nice of you

21:35.327 --> 21:37.295
to discard all those queens.

21:38.731 --> 21:40.028
I don't want
to play anymore, Marion.

21:40.166 --> 21:42.328
I'm going to bed.

21:42.468 --> 21:44.459
You gave me four queens
in a row.

21:44.603 --> 21:46.594
Don't start, Marion.

21:51.610 --> 21:52.702
Thanks for everything, Ralph.

21:52.845 --> 21:54.813
It was fun.
I really had a good time.

21:54.947 --> 21:56.176
Yes, so did I.

21:56.315 --> 21:58.306
And you want to know
what the best part was?

21:58.450 --> 22:00.646
Nobody expected me
to clown around for once.

22:00.786 --> 22:03.221
And I really enjoyed
dressing up.

22:03.355 --> 22:04.447
You know something, Leather?

22:04.590 --> 22:05.716
You look great in a formal.

22:05.858 --> 22:07.223
I mean, you really fit right in.

22:07.359 --> 22:09.657
Well, how about you? You didn't
crack one joke all night.

22:09.795 --> 22:11.058
I know.

22:11.197 --> 22:13.461
And the thing is that people
accepted me that way.

22:13.599 --> 22:15.363
I mean, everyone still liked me.

22:15.501 --> 22:17.833
I was so boring!

22:17.970 --> 22:19.438
I hated myself tonight!

22:19.572 --> 22:20.596
I wasn't any fun.

22:20.739 --> 22:22.764
Not one laugh.

22:22.908 --> 22:23.841
Well, what about me?

22:23.976 --> 22:25.910
Not one...

22:26.045 --> 22:27.638
I was only pretending, too.

22:27.780 --> 22:29.145
And you know what?

22:29.281 --> 22:31.682
I've had a nail stuck
in my heel all evening.

22:31.817 --> 22:33.945
Look.

22:34.086 --> 22:35.520
Are you kidding me?

22:35.654 --> 22:36.849
(laughter)

22:36.989 --> 22:38.753
That's great.

22:38.891 --> 22:40.086
You know something, Leather?

22:40.226 --> 22:41.716
You may have a nail
in your heel,

22:41.861 --> 22:43.192
but you've got a lot of sole.

22:43.329 --> 22:44.524
(laughter)

22:44.663 --> 22:46.654
I've still got it,
I've still got it!

22:46.799 --> 22:48.858
Yes, even in retirement,

22:49.001 --> 22:50.435
I've still got it.

22:50.569 --> 22:52.401
Boy, I've got to tell you,

22:52.538 --> 22:54.063
I'm glad we told each other
the truth.

22:54.206 --> 22:55.674
Yeah, me too, and you know what?

22:55.808 --> 22:58.607
The next time we go out,
we can be ourselves.

22:58.744 --> 22:59.768
You know it.

22:59.912 --> 23:01.107
But will we ever find
an honor guard

23:01.247 --> 23:02.715
with their arms up again...

23:02.848 --> 23:04.782
We can try, Ralph.

23:04.917 --> 23:06.578
All right, all right.

23:06.719 --> 23:08.244
Listen, I got to go.

23:08.387 --> 23:09.718
You know, I feel really naked.

23:09.855 --> 23:11.914
I'm going to go home
and get my rubber nose.

23:12.057 --> 23:13.115
Ralph,

23:13.259 --> 23:15.557
you forgot something.

23:15.694 --> 23:17.685
Oh.

23:17.830 --> 23:19.821
Of course.

23:26.972 --> 23:28.303
Thanks.

23:28.440 --> 23:30.568
You know,
both Ralph Malphs are sweet.

23:30.709 --> 23:34.043
So are both Leather Tuscaderos.

23:34.179 --> 23:36.170
- Good night.
- Good night.

23:42.254 --> 23:44.655
Wait till I kiss you
with my rubber nose on.

23:55.467 --> 23:56.832
Oh, Joanie.

23:56.969 --> 23:57.902
- Hi, Mom and Dad.
- Hi, sweetheart.

23:58.037 --> 23:59.334
Did you have a nice evening?

23:59.471 --> 24:00.632
No.

24:00.773 --> 24:02.366
It's happened the third night
in a row.

24:02.508 --> 24:03.771
I'm going to break off
with Smitty.

24:03.909 --> 24:06.139
Oh, dear, and he seemed
like such a nice boy.

24:06.278 --> 24:07.473
What happened, sweetheart?

24:07.613 --> 24:09.206
Well, we were going
to Inspiration Point

24:09.348 --> 24:11.316
to look at the Big Dipper
through his telescope.

24:11.450 --> 24:12.781
- Yeah?
- And you know what happened?

24:12.918 --> 24:15.285
- What?
- We looked at the Big Dipper.

24:15.421 --> 24:18.413
If you've seen one Milky Way,
you've seen them all!

24:21.427 --> 24:22.861
Howard, she's turning out

24:22.995 --> 24:24.690
just like your side
of the family.

24:26.298 --> 24:28.096
We'll have to have
a talk with her.

24:28.233 --> 24:30.725
Oh, I wouldn't worry
about that, sweetheart.

24:30.869 --> 24:34.305
Not as long as Smitty
carries that telescope.

24:34.440 --> 24:36.568
Marion, it's your move.

24:36.709 --> 24:38.973
Oh, I just love marbles, Howard.

24:39.111 --> 24:41.205
It's Chinese Checkers, Marion.

24:41.347 --> 24:43.475
Well...

24:43.615 --> 24:44.707
whatever it is,

24:44.850 --> 24:48.150
I've got all my marbles
in your little triangle.

24:49.188 --> 24:50.349
I know that.

24:50.489 --> 24:52.389
What are you going
to teach me tomorrow night?

24:52.524 --> 24:54.993
Solitaire, Marion.

